{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44/comments/3130358.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44#comment-3130358"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 44, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-legacy", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-legacy", "uuid": "{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}"}, "title": "Next version of cloudsim should include a feature \"upgrade\""}, "content": {"raw": "That is an interesting point, and we don't have plans to address it. \nAs of CloudSim 1.2, It is not possible for a constellation to \"adopt\" a running field computer.\n\nNote:\nIt is important to keep in mind that setup of the field computer should be automated as much as possible, because DARPA will launch the constellations from their own AWS account, and attaching field computers from different accounts will not be supported. Teams will have time set aside to prepare their \"new\" field computer before running a set of tasks.\n\nwork around:\nUse ssh to login the simulator and perform ROS, drcsim and gazebo upgrades using apt-get, just like you would on the field computer.\nThis should breathe new life to old constellations. \n\ncaveat:\nThis technique won't address changes in constellation network topology, iptables, VPN settings etc.\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>That is an interesting point, and we don't have plans to address it. \nAs of CloudSim 1.2, It is not possible for a constellation to \"adopt\" a running field computer.</p>\n<p>Note:\nIt is important to keep in mind that setup of the field computer should be automated as much as possible, because DARPA will launch the constellations from their own AWS account, and attaching field computers from different accounts will not be supported. Teams will have time set aside to prepare their \"new\" field computer before running a set of tasks.</p>\n<p>work around:\nUse ssh to login the simulator and perform ROS, drcsim and gazebo upgrades using apt-get, just like you would on the field computer.\nThis should breathe new life to old constellations. </p>\n<p>caveat:\nThis technique won't address changes in constellation network topology, iptables, VPN settings etc.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-02-14T01:21:24.384346+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Hugo Boyer", "uuid": "{3d87874e-7099-4981-b04f-57f0272faa7d}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d87874e-7099-4981-b04f-57f0272faa7d%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d87874e-7099-4981-b04f-57f0272faa7d%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/21198da8539b599e3633017f5f5f8150d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsHB-6.png"}}, "nickname": "hugomatic", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:869c02bb-b246-4cdc-9db3-0064e8add185"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 3130358}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44/comments/4055060.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44#comment-4055060"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy/issues/44.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 44, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/cloudsim-legacy.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/cloudsim-legacy"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "cloudsim-legacy", "full_name": "osrf/cloudsim-legacy", "uuid": "{e799e7f6-0caa-464a-97f8-8605a37ebfb1}"}, "title": "Next version of cloudsim should include a feature \"upgrade\""}, "co